Vice President Kamala Harris convened a meeting with Florida state legislators to discuss and protect reproductive rights. She was joined by Secretary of Health and Human Services Xavier Becerra. The Vice President emphasized the government's commitment to protecting access to reproductive health care, including abortion access. She encouraged the legislators to continue fighting for reproductive rights in Florida. The meeting also addressed the harmful impact of Florida's abortion restrictions and the overwhelming effect of abortion bans in other southern states on Florida's health systems. The Vice President recognized the importance of building coalitions to defend rights and freedoms and reaffirmed the commitment to working together to protect reproductive rights for all women in Florida and the nation.